 of mistakes made.  I then came home and logged on my computer, another repetition of life.  But regardless of the cycles of life, I always try to learn something new and always try to learn from Life's mistakes.  I'm posting today to prevent another repetitious mistake, one of inaction, silence, and apathy.<br><br>I've played EQ since its dawn and observed events transpire and evolve as all things do.  I hope that at the end of 3 years, I've learned something from it and evolved into something better than I was, in game and in life.  <br><br>One thing however remains clear, some people have not learned from their mistakes and remain unchanged as they had 8 months ago.  <br><br>I will remind people that 8 months ago was the day the World Trade Center fell to the Earth and over two thousand (2000) people of all faiths and all races died that day.  <br><br>There are things that happen in the world that are larger and greater than what we experience in casual day to day life.. and then there are events too immense to comprehend where lives are changed forever.  <br><br>I remind you all that the lives you touch through ether space are human lives.  Some of you will remain callous to that fact and for you, you have my pity.  The others of you that have the capability to feel shame and remorse have the ability to change for the better.  Every day you wake, you have the ability to make a choice and therefore to evolve and become something great.  <br><br>Still everyday I log on and review these boards and see how much some haven't changed at all nor learned anything of the world in which they live.  Petty bickering over pixels that don't matter, endless harping over the same topics, espousal of the same rhetoric.  Perched on lofty branches of arrogance and supreme intellect.  Secure in the armor of their own vane opinions which they claim to be the only Truth.  They are Right, condemn all dissenters as heretics.  Lines are then drawn and verbal wars rage.  Does this sound familiar?  <br><br>Terrorists are of the same mind set as you but where they are very wrong is they take this war one step further and involve the lives of innocent people.  They do not compromise, they will not listen to reason.  Sound familiar yet?<br><br>Verbal terrorism.  Attacks on each other's humanity in the name of what you believe to be the only Truth, your Truth.  <br><br>Have you learned anything yet?<br><br><br><br>I sit here at this computer and mourn not only those who died but the millions of surviving friends and family that died in the wake of 911.  Because some things are more important than this.<br><br>There will continue to be jackals waiting to pull their fellow EQ gamers down, there will continue to be people out on a witch hunt to burn the heretics for past real and imagined offenses.  There will be people that will not forgive no matter what.  There will be people whose intolerance for other opinions, races, faiths will continue to strike at monuments and symbols you hold dear.  I suppose the only question I have for you, is will you learn from these mistakes?  Will you change?<br><br>My message will no doubt be lost upon some people.  Some board harpies will no doubt see this as an attack somehow and defend their position with rhetoric and doublespeak as their sword and shield.  Doubtless others will miscontrue what I say and take words out of context and see conspiracies where none exist.  Those of you that can reach that spark of humanity within though and be better, I'll see you at the end of the Journey in which we wake.<br><br><br>It is my hope that everyone who reads this will be able to feel as I, how rare and precious a Gift all Life is.  To be able to feel the Grace inherent in each person that enables them to be better than they are....  to give each other compassion, tolerance, respect and finally forgiveness.  That continues to be my hope.<br><br>Warren<br><br><br><br><br><br> <p></p><i></i>