d to just Do the Right Thing.  A woman and her mother in a car see a Motorcyclist lying bleeding on the street. The woman is one week from getting her medical license, and could have helped the man.  Her mother was afraid she'd get sued for practicing without a license, and so they drove on.  <br><br>And as far as 9/11 is concerned, I understand that what happened was a horrible thing, and quite needless.  However, it happened.  And not to sound crass, but aside from a two hour line at the aiport, and just a little more bigotry disguised as 'sensitivity', there really *isn't* much affect in the daily lives of the average American, or maybe more specifically, EQers (aside from those who've lost people to the attack or course).   If you put a M1 battle tank in the parking lot of an office building, it gathers attention.  If you leave it for a week, it becomes part of the landscape.  This is simply the way the human mind works, and has nothing to do with poeple's care for what happened.<br><br>As for Lurikeen's comment on nuclear war in the Indian sub-continent: "I don't think it'll happen" ... nobody thought 9/11 was going to happen, either, did they?  The euphamism 'Nobody in their right minds would....' is naive.  Even if the vast majority of humans on this planet know that something is Not Right, there are those that think their version of Right is worth the lives of others.<br><br>No matter what happens where, what religion you follow, or your Geographic location, if everyone simply followed the Golden Rule....  <p>-Jabener Half-elven<BR>Ranger of Karana<BR><BR><center><img src="http://www.burningmoon.net/images/Jabener.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uaishen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aishen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br